posts.description:
Unless you’re a doctor, lawyer, architect, engineer or something which legally requires a certificate of tertiary qualification, the need for that piece of paper is diminishing at a rapid rate.
-
The question of “where did you go to school” is becoming more and more irrelevant with the increase in online learning and availability of free knowledge.
-
Don’t be fooled into thing that you are inadequate because you lack a $100k student loan for a piece of paper which is really only proof of theoretical knowledge in a field or profession.
-
I would rather hire a designer with 100 satisfied clients in a portfolio than a person who has completed a degree at a prestigious school but yet to apply their skills in the real world. #globalshift
